We start by computing each ratio from the provided statements.

1. ROE (Return on Equity):
 • Net Profit = 905750.76 (from the income statement)
 • Total Owner's Equity = 13905750.76 (from the balance sheet)
 • ROE = Net Profit / Total Owner's Equity = 905750.76 / 13905750.76 ≈ 0.0652 or 6.52%

2. Debt to Asset Ratio:
 • Total Liabilities = Total Assets – Total Owner's Equity = 14534228.78 – 13905750.76 = 628478.02
 • Total Assets = 14534228.78
 • Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets = 628478.02 / 14534228.78 ≈ 0.0433 (rounded to 0.04 when expressed as in the example)

3. Gross Profit Margin:
 • Gross Profit = 1620560.42 (from the income statement)
 • Total Revenue = 2869560.42
 • Gross Profit Margin = Gross Profit / Total Revenue = 1620560.42 / 2869560.42 ≈ 0.5649 or 56.49%

Thus, the final answer in the requested JSON format is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Return on Equity (ROE)": "6.52%",
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.04",
    "Gross Profit Margin": "56.49%"
  }
}
